* Enter Gun Time for 5k Race Prompt
*
*   When to use:    Just once at the starting gun.
*   How to use:     Double-click to open the dialog box, then enter your time
*                   (HH:MM:SS.ss format). The dialog writes the value into the
*                   GunStart database field only — it does not update the
*                   GunStart event by itself.
*   Alternative:    Edit @GUNTIME.2.O.lst or setgunstart.rsm directly, then run
*                   GunStart2Event.2.O.lst to copy the field into the event.
*
*   This listing uses Continue (see docs: Continue command) so processing does
*   not stop after the dialog; the steps below then push GunStart field → event.


select              Race
=                   5k
selected            GunStart
selected Message    ?ENTER Gun Time and click OK Format MUST BE HH:MM:SS.ss

* Continue — without this, the listing stops after Selected and GunStart event
*            is never updated even though the dialog saved the database field.
Continue

* Database to Event — copies the GunStart field value (from the dialog above)
*                     into the GunStart event for all matching runners.
Database to Event
Initialize Times
Event               GunStart
Database Field      GunStart
Select              GunStart
<>
